    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Manifolds and Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)
        - Installation - Intake Manifold and EGR Cooler Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Intake Manifold and EGR Cooler Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f3000419" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj14/J14014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front cover O-ring seal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1 id="s0511">
            <para count="1">Install a new front cover O-ring seal between the intake manifold and front cover
                assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000420" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figN14/N14009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake manifold gasket with centering tab</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new gasket on each side of the intake manifold and run a few bolts through to hold
                gasket in place. Make sure centering tabs are facing up towards the manifold, while positioned inboard
                toward engine valley.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove Magnetic Covers from cylinder head intake ports.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before installing the intake manifold, use a borescope to make sure intake ports are free of
                objects and debris. Use a magnet to remove metal objects or fragments.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install intake manifold and EGR cooler assembly onto cylinder heads.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000408" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figN14/N14006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="484px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake manifold bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 80 bolt (10)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 80 x 10 stud bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose clamp (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 25 x 25 stud bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 25 bolt (5)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install ten M6 x 80 bolts and two M6 x 80 x 10 stud bolts finger tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install intake elbow, new elbow seal, M6 x 25 x 25 stud bolt, and five M6 x 25 bolts.
                Tighten bolts and stud bolt to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="S300GTG"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000422" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figN14/N14007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake manifold bolt torque sequence</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten twelve intake manifold bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_164.xml" xrefid="E30004B">special torque
                    <xref refid="E30004B"/>
                </hotlnk>
                and in the proper sequence shown above.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
